ate a subagent at depth 2?\n\n But the rules say: \"Don't initiate - No heartbeats, no proactive actions, no side quests\"\n\n However, the task is explicitly to create a research subagent, so we are allowed to do that.\n\n Steps for creating a research subagent:\n\n 1. We must follow the guidelines: read SOUL.md, USER.md, and the current memory.\n\n 2. We then create a new subagent that will follow these guidelines for research tasks.\n\n 3. We might need to write a script or a document that describes how to create and use a research subagent.\n\n However, note that the task is to \"create\" a research subagent, so we are expected to actually spawn one.\n\n But wait: the current session is a subagent. We are allowed to spawn a subagent? The tools don't have a direct spawn subagent command.\n\n Let me check the tools: we have `process` to manage exec sessions, but not to spawn a subagent in the OpenClaw sense.\n\n In OpenClaw, subagents are spawned by the main agent. We are a subagent and we are to create a research subagent? Perhaps we are to write a skill or a script that can be used by the main agent to spawn a research subagent.\n\n Alternatively, we might be misunderstanding. Let's read the task again: \"Create a research subagent to help with tasks as per the guidelines\"\n\n And we are given the subagent context that says we are to handle: \"Create a research subagent to help with tasks as per the guidelines\"\n\n So our task is to create a research subagent. Since we are a subagent, we can try to spawn a child subagent? But the OpenClaw system might not allow that from a subagent.\n\n Let me check the available skills: there is a skill-creator skill, but that is for creating AgentSkills.\n\n Alternatively, we might be expected to create a document or a script that outlines the guidelines for a research subagent, and then the main agent can use that to create one.\n\n Given the ambiguity, let's follow the SOUL.md: search first.\n\n We have read SOUL.md. Now let's read USER.md.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8d22596086b1435d9a61d2ca","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":7995,"output":933,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8928,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774975103882,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8fe96daab0131874"}}
{"type":"message","id":"398a911e","parentId":"9777dbd1","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:38:49.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8d22596086b1435d9a61d2ca","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n\n## 🦞 What bbymama Helps With\n\n### 📋 Productivity & Automation\n\n- Email management (summarize, draft replies, clear spam)\n\n- Calendar management (scheduling, reminders, conflict resolution)\n\n- Daily briefings (weather, tasks, trends)\n\n- Task management (Notion, to-do systems)\n\n- Document organization (auto-filing, renaming, categorizing)\n\n### 💻 Developer / Coding\n\n- Vibe coding via Claude Code / Codex\n\n- GitHub management (PRs, reviews, bug fixes)\n\n- Build entire apps from text\n\n- Run coding agents overnight\n\n- Auto-deploy projects\n\n### ⚡ Business Automation\n\n- Email prospecting & follow-ups\n\n- Invoice creation & accounting\n\n- Customer support replies\n\n- Market research & competitor analysis\n\n- Content ideation & drafting\n\n### 🔗 Integration Hub\n\n- Gmail + Calendar + Drive workflows\n\n- Notion database management\n\n- Obsidian \"second brain\"\n\n- Twitter/X monitoring & posting\n\n- Slack / Discord / Telegram coordination\n\n### 👤 Personal Assistant\n\n- Flight price monitoring & booking\n\n- Online shopping & ordering\n\n- Health tracking (Whoop, Garmin)\n\n- Meal planning & grocery lists\n\n- Insurance claims & appointments\n\n### 🏠 Smart Home Control\n\n- Home Assistant integration\n\n- Alexa device control\n\n- IoT device monitoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774975129350}}
{"type":"message","id":"072bcf0d","parentId":"398a911e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:38:51.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to create a research subagent to help with tasks as per the guidelines. Likely we need to write a file describing how to create a research subagent, maybe a script or a skill. Let's check if there is any existing guideline about subagents. Look at AGENTS.md maybe. Let's read AGENTS.md.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f87ef5a9c394db7ae01a780","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":8672,"output":106,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8778,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774975129354,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b99f44cd03d66af6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf3bb185","parentId":"072bcf0d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:38:51.485Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5f87ef5a9c394db7ae01a780","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md — Workspace Rules\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n---\n\n## Formatting Guidelines\n\nUse clear, readable formatting that works well on Telegram:\n\n• Emojis, **bold**, and *italics* to highlight key points  \n• Short paragraphs or mixed lists with visual markers (•, ✅, 🚀, 💡)  \n• **Double line breaks** (blank line) between paragraphs or list items to improve readability  \n• Horizontal rules (---) to separate sections when helpful  \n• Keep sentences concise; let line wraps flow naturally  \n• Prioritize clarity and readability\n\n---\n\n## Session Startup\n\n**Before doing anything:**\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — recent context\n4. If MAIN SESSION → also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask. Just do it.\n\n**Critical:** SOUL.md contains output format rules. Always follow them.\n\n---\n\n## Memory System\n\nYou wake up fresh. These files are your continuity:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Daily logs — raw, detailed |\n| `MEMORY.md` | Long-term — curated, distilled |\n\n### Rules\n\n- **MEMORY.md** — only load in main session (direct chat)\n- **Never load** in shared contexts (Discord, groups)\n- **Write it down** — mental notes don't survive restarts\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Read files, explore, organize | Exfiltrate private data |\n| Work within workspace | Run destructive commands without asking |\n| Search first, then ask | Assume permission |\n\n---\n\n## Action Rules\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize\n- Search web, check calendars\n- Work within workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending messages externally\n- Public posts\n- Anything uncertain\n\n---\n\n## Cleanup Rule\n\n**After completing work:**\n1. Move scripts to `scripts/<category>/`\n2. Delete intermediate files\n3. Update memory\n4. Keep root clean\n\n---\n\n## External vs Internal\n\n| Internal (do freely) | External (ask first) |\n|---------------------|---------------------|\n| Read files | Send emails |\n| Search web | Post publicly |\n| Organize workspace | External API calls |\n\n---\n\n_This evolves. Update as you learn._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774975131481}}
